
Readme file for: LSF
Product/Component Release: 9.1.2
Publication date: 21 October 2013
Last modified: 21 October 2013

Access IBM Platform Computing's LSF Batch API from Perl.



================
CONTENTS
================
 
 Overview
 Version History
 Copyright



================
Overview
================

LSF 9.1.2 supports Perl APIs. 
Most of the functions in the API have been implemented and tested, but
the formal test.pl has not been extensively tested. This works on 
Solaris 2.X, AIX 4.3, Linux and Tru64.



================
Version History
================

- Version 0.01 4/04/2000:
  First public release. Some functions were not totally debugged and not
  completely tested.

- Version 0.02 4/05/2000:
  Added README to the MANIFEST.

- Version 0.03 6/01/2000:
  Library works on Solaris. Several bugs were fixed.

- Version 0.04 4/13/2001:
  General improvements. Added support for lsb_geteventrec. 
  Added a script to help generate XS code from LSF include files (makexs.pl)

- Version 0.05 4/29/2008:
  Based on Version 0.05, some enhancements for APIs were added to support 
  LSF 7.0 Update 2. All the APIs have been tested in test.pl on Linux 2.6
  and Solaris 10(X86_64) by Perl 5.8.0.

- Version 0.06 6/13/2008:
  Added 10 new APIs. These APIs were tested in test.pl on linux2.6 and Solaris 10(X86_64) 
  by Perl 5.8.0. Added test_launch.pl to test two special APIs: lsb_gethostlist and lsb_launch.
  test.pl can be used as normal. test_launch.pl is used in test.pl.
  Added the document for the APIs, which can be viewed with perldoc.



